text.section:
In addition to any other powers or duties provided for elsewhere in this title, the Board may:
establish guidelines for creating new bargaining units that include a consideration of:
the effect of overfragmentation on the employer;
the administrative structures of the State employer;
the recommendations of the parties;
the recommendations of the Executive Director;
the desires of the employees involved;
the communities of interest of the employees involved; and
the wages, hours, and other working conditions of the employees;
establish standards for determining an appropriate bargaining unit; and
investigate and resolve disputes about appropriate bargaining units;
establish procedures for, supervise the conduct of, and resolve disputes about elections for exclusive representatives; and
investigate and take appropriate action in response to complaints of unfair labor practices and lockouts.
